index_struct.text: This code file provides three query classes for vector store indices: GPTFaissIndexQuery, GPTSimpleVectorIndexQuery, and GPTWeaviateIndexQuery. These classes are used to query vector store indices and retrieve relevant data. The query classes use different algorithms and data structures to search the indices and return the desired results. GPTFaissIndexQuery uses Faiss, an open-source library for efficient similarity search and clustering of dense vectors, to search the indices. GPTSimpleVectorIndexQuery uses a simple vector search algorithm to search the indices. GPTWeaviateIndexQuery uses Weaviate, an open-source knowledge graph engine, to search the indices. The purpose of this code is to provide an easy way to query vector store indices and access the data stored in them.

from gpt_index.indices.query.vector_store.simple import GPTSimpleVectorIndexQuery
from gpt_index.indices.query.vector_store.weaviate import GPTWeaviateIndexQuery

__all__ = ["GPTFaissIndexQuery", "GPTSimpleVectorIndexQuery", "GPTWeaviateIndexQuery"]
